sub_title: Marketing Operations & Communications Manager at FeelRobotics
summary:
I am a communications professional with a Bachelor of Science (B.Sc.) focused in International Communications and Media from Erasmus University Rotterdam. Skilled with a strong affinity for Online Marketing, Communication, Copywriting and Public Relations. 

Currently, I work in the field of high-tech haptics and robotics. We use technology to help our customers forge new and better ways to communicate, because in an increasingly digitized world, the need grows every day. 

Aside from work, I am a curious individual, who loves to travel, meet new people and explore different cultures.

projects:
[{'title': 'Social Media Marketing Project', 'date': {'start': {'month': 4, 'day': None, 'year': 2013}, 'end': {'month': 6, 'day': None, 'year': 2013}}, 'description': 'For my Communication Management class at Erasmus University Rotterdam, i was required to conduct a social media marketing project with my partner. Our company of choice was Boguette a popular Vietnamese baguette shop in Rotterdam. 

The project involved: 
Analysing the use of new media in business communications, along with their contemporary concerns regarding Web 2.0 technologies. 
So from here, we found a company and interview the owner about their current business model, as well as their social media usage. We found the best points of the business as well as the main challenges the business endures in terms of social media, as well as the benefits they can get from being active on social media. We then did a synthesis of customer perceptions, contrasting this to company perceptions on the challenges in business communication using social media. Last but not least, we came up with Social Media Marketing Campaigns in order to further the success of this business.

I developed skills in:
Analysing and evaluating (research on) the role of new media in business communication, empirically examining new business models and new modes of communication, translation of theoretical notions into an empirical research design, applying relevant research methods and techniques covered throughout the course, and report our research findings in a scientifically substantiated manner in order to provide relevant feedback for the manager of Boguette upon completion of our project.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Ashton', 'last_name': 'Egner', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Marketing Operations & Communications Manager at FeelRobotics'}]}]
